Just a little update here 4 anyone who'se reading thru these comments looking for an installer for "Overland Fly! Into The Sky":
It turns out that my "installer" is not a complete package, but rather just the .msi module... which, unfortulately, requires a support package (installer .exe) be useful. So as of this post, I NO NOT have an installer for it. :-( Sorry folks.
SK

Hi,

The original installer is not needed for the patch.

All you need is a msi extract tool like LessMSIerables.

Do the following to install the patch:

1. Start the patch (it is a InstallShield wizard). It will complain because the original package is not installed . Do not close the installer!

2. Check the \Documents and Setting\YourProfile\LocalSettings\Temp folder
The installer extract its content to this folder.
Search for a .msi file with the size of 98588672 bytes.

3. Copy this file to somewhere else.
You can exit the installer as soon as the file copied. The installer will delet the file from the TEMP folder.

4. Open the msi file with LessMSIerables and extract the content.

5. Overwrite the files in FS9\Aircraft and FS9\Gaguges folder.

BR,
Zsiraf
